# Hub login accounts (42c.pw + c42.io)

Aria provisions website logins with the `create_42c_account` tool in
[`src/tools.py`](src/tools.py). 42c.pw (the gated hub) and the c42.io login form
run on ONE nginx and share ONE credential file, so a single account works for
both. Do not build a second account path.

## The credential has one home

`c42_public/.htpasswd` (apr1 hashes) is the single home for every login. The
plaintext admin credential lives once in the repo-root `.env`
(`HUB_BASIC_AUTH_USER` / `HUB_BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD`); `.htpasswd` is its hashed
copy. Rotation edits both in the same change.

- NEVER bake a password into `c42_public/Dockerfile` (no `RUN htpasswd -b ...`).
  The image only `COPY`s `.htpasswd` in; a baked password leaks in an image layer.
- NEVER ask the user for the password and never improvise `openssl`/`htpasswd`
  shell commands. `create_42c_account` is the only writer of `.htpasswd`.

## The flow (already implemented — do not reinvent)

`create_42c_account(username, password)`:
1. `_apr1_hash` — `openssl passwd -apr1` (the format nginx reads).
2. `_upsert_htpasswd` — idempotent add/replace of the `user:hash` line.
3. deploy — runs the **repo-root** `deploy.sh` (NOT `c42_public/deploy.sh`,
   which does not exist). It bakes `c42_public` into the `alive-river` Fly image.
4. `_verify_42c_login` — curls the live site with the new creds.

The deploy needs flyctl plus the sibling repos the root `deploy.sh` stages
(`alive_river`, `live_visuals_4`, the protein venv). If those are missing the
deploy fails loudly — surface the error, don't swallow it.

## Verify

`python scripts/e2e_42c_invite.py --no-deploy --no-send` for a dry run, or no
flags for the real create-account-then-text path.
